<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Not JUST that. Let's FLAME -PvP a sec too</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ndaven">Ndaven</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:27 a.m. 22/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Not JUST that. Let's FLAME -PvP a sec too<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1126" TARGET=_self>Not JUST that. Let's FLAME -PvP a sec too</A> (Gray Rage (DB))
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> When I was playin' on the -PvP server in P3 no one paid ANY

<BR>&gt; attention to race whatsoever! NEVER! I consistantly aided and
<BR>&gt; was aided by races that should have been natural enemies!
<BR>&gt; Additionally, I never once even thought of using the language
<BR>&gt; abilties provided. Why should I have? There were no enemies in
<BR>&gt; the game and as such what would I have to hide when shouting?
<P>&gt; 1. Factions are needed to make the server have some continuity
<BR>&gt; and organization, to ensure that the players have a reasonably
<BR>&gt; safe home area and that newb waxing is not prevalent.
<P>I certaintly agree with this. I lost count of the number of dark elves I have seen wandering in Freeport and the outlying areas on Ro. Seems to me that those races shouldn't be just waltzing into a human city without challenge. Of course, I did see some dark elf bodies lying on the streets once...
<P>There are, however, people who do follow races. I was lucky enough to witness a few human/dark elf duels in the east commonlands (from the safety of a nice hiding place, of course... I may not like the dark elves, but I ain't stupid! :) Remember, not all the people who stick to -PvP are doing it for 'roleplaying' reasons... and many of them may not even have a good idea of what a 'dark elf' or 'troll' is in social relation to, say, a high elf. Many of the people are there simply to have fun...and if you don't like being killed by others, well....
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
